<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Ericameria</i> <i>ericoides</i> and <i>Lupinus</i> <i>chamissonis</i> occur characteristically together or alone in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>pycnocephala</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> <i>arboreus</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>littoralis</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i> and <i>Toxicodendron</i> <i>diversilobum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Lupinus chamissonis</i> and/or <i>Ericameria ericoides</i> are conspicuous (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Ericameria ericoides</i> and/or <i>Lupinus chamissonis</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy, or in combination with each other > 30% relative cover with <i>Baccharis pilularis</i> or <i>Lupinus arboreus</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stabilized dunes of coastal bars, river mouths, spits along coastlines, coastal bluffs, and terraces.  </div>
</div>

        
